    "And more importantly, this is a case where the positive and negative classes in the data are more or less balanced.",
    "To be precise, the corresponding prevalence is 0.452.",
    "When data becomes more imbalanced and either the positive or negative class dominates the data, different metrics' evaluation behavior can be very different.",
    "To obtain a more complete picture of the dynamics between prevalence level and model evaluation by different metrics, we use statistical simulation to create a series of data sets with varying prevalence.",
